    <p>
        <span class="bold italic">Dr. Zak Saleh, DVM, MVSc, PhD</span><br />
        Dr. Zak has been practicing veterinary medicine for more than 20 years, graduating from veterinary college in 1989, has completed his postgraduate studies at the same college, from which received his MVSc, & Doctorate degrees.
        He is our hospital veterinarian/owner and director. He has worked in many animal hospitals in Ontario. His work in emergency hospitals gives him the opportunity to work on a large variety of critical cases and saved hundreds of animals lives.
        He loves the day to day interactions with his employees, clients, and patients. "There is nothing more satisfying than saving pets lives or improving their quality of life.”
        Dr. Zak loves every animal that walks through the door
        as if it was his own. He feels that every animal should
        receive the best care available and that is what he provides.
        If Dr. Zak’s patients could speak they would tell you what great care they received from the most methodical, compassionate doctor that they know.
        Dr. Zak has many hobbies that vary greatly but what he finds makes his life truly satisfying is treating and curing patients and spending time with his family.
        His interest is soft tissue surgery, emergency & critical care, internal medicine
